  "harness/README.md": "# gdc-snap-test-harness

Standalone development harness for **gdc-snap-test-module**.

This is a template. Run \`rush init-pluggable-app\` to scaffold a new application from it.

## What this does

The harness runs the pluggable application module outside of the full host shell. It provides:

- A Vite dev server with backend API proxying
- Local application registration (the module is lazy-loaded the same way the host would load it)
- GoodData UI Kit CSS and Indigo font
- HTTPS support via local certificates (optional)

## Development

\`\`\`bash
# Copy environment template and fill in your API token
cp .env.template .env

# Start dev server
rushx dev
\`\`\`

The server starts at \`https://localhost:<port>\`. Navigate to the appropriate scope URL:

- **Organization-scoped apps**: \`https://localhost:<port>/organization/<route>\`
- **Workspace-scoped apps**: \`https://localhost:<port>/workspace/<workspaceId>/<route>\`

## Configuration

| Variable          | Default       | Description                            |
| ----------------- | ------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| \`BACKEND_URL\`     | _(required)_  | GoodData backend to proxy API calls to |
| \`TIGER_API_TOKEN\` | _(required)_  | API token for authentication           |
| \`PORT\`            | 8450 | Dev server port                        |

## Build

\`\`\`bash
rushx build
\`\`\`

Produces a production bundle in \`dist/\`.
",
  "harness/config/rush-project.json": "{
    "$schema": "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/rush/v5/rush-project.schema.json",
    "incrementalBuildIgnoredGlobs": [],
    "operationSettings": [
        {
            "operationName": "_phase:build",
            "outputFolderNames": ["dist"]
        },
        {
            "operationName": "_phase:validate",
            "outputFolderNames": []
        },
        {
            "operationName": "_phase:test",
            "outputFolderNames": []
        },
        {
            // The scaffolder-injected \`_phase:pack-build\` (see internalProfile.ts) builds the
            // harness shell into <app>-harness.tgz and copies the sibling module's federation
            // remote \`../module/gdc-snap-test-pluggable.tgz\` in as <app>-remote.tgz —
            // both ADDed by the harness Dockerfile. The harness depends on its sibling module as
            // a workspace dep, so Rush runs the module's _phase:pack-build first. If that dep edge
            // is ever removed, the copy will fail with ENOENT — fix the dep, not the script.
            "operationName": "_phase:pack-build",
            "outputFolderNames": [],
            "disableBuildCacheForOperation": true
        },
        {
            "operationName": "_phase:publish-test-docker-images",
            "outputFolderNames": [],
            "disableBuildCacheForOperation": true
        }
    ]
}
",
